Lieutenant General H.R. McMaster, President Donald J. Trump’s National Security Advisor, met with Ambassador İbrahim Kalın, Deputy Secretary General and Spokesperson of the Turkish Presidency, during his visit to Istanbul. The purpose of the meeting was to affirm the long-term strategic partnership between the United States and Turkey and discuss the priorities and concerns of both countries. They also exchanged views on American-Turkish relations as longstanding allies, common strategic challenges, and regional developments. The two leaders addressed issues affecting bilateral relations in detail and explored ways to expand the joint fight against all forms of terrorism.